<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Simpson College</h2>
<strong>Indianola, IA</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>A student who receives a score of 3, 4, or 5 on any College Entrance Examination Board Advanced Placement Exam (AP) is given credit for the equivalent Simpson course.  A student may earn up to 24 semester hours of credit by examination in these courses.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://simpson.edu/registrar/clepap-credit/advanced-placement-ap-credit/" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

